itics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aPolitical Studies 2019. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Movements / Critical Theory.2bisacsh  aAffect.  aCritical theory.  aErnst Bloch.  aFeeling.  aFrankfurt School.  aHappiness.  aHope.  aInstitute for Social Research.  aMelancholy.  aTheodor Adorno.  aWalter Benjamin.  aaesthetics.  aaffective politics.  aaffective turn.  aarts and humanities.  aconscious unhappiness.  amelancholia.  amimesis.  apolitics of hope.  apost-Cold War triumphalism.  asocial critique.1 aMussell, Simon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packagez978311128281740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612201840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526122018423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526122018/original  a978-3-11-128281-7  Manchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packageb2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles